HEADWORD: Orbicular
<hw>Or*bic"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>orbicularis</ets>, fr. <ets>orbiculus</ets>, dim. of
<ets>orbis</ets> orb: cf. F. <ets>orbiculaire</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Resembling or having the form of an orb; spherical; circular;
orbiculate.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Or*bic"u*lar*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Or*bic"u*lar*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Orbicular</qex> as the disk of a planet.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orbiculate</ent>⟦br⟧
